The Robin Hood Foundation  recently received bags of  pre-loved clothing from learners of Westville Girls’ High School. The school handed over more than 60 bags which will be used for the foundations next Mahala Market for gogo and mkhulu’s and their families. Kim Griffith Jones, co-ordinator at RHF said, “A huge thank you to the staff and learners for their generosity. These clothes will be used at our next market where community members will be invited to shop for free.” To know more about donating and collecting pre-loved clothing for the Robin Hood Foundation, contact Kim Griffth Jones on info@robinhoodfoundation.co.za